Class ColorPaletteRecord

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gridfour.imaging.palette.ColorPaletteRecord
  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    ColorPaletteRecordHSV, ColorPaletteRecordRGB

    public abstract class ColorPaletteRecord
extends Object
implements Comparable<ColorPaletteRecord>
    The abstract base class for color-palette entries using various color models.

      • getArgb

        public abstract int getArgb(double z)
        Gets an ARGB value for the specified parameter, if available. Implementations of this method generally expect that the value for z will be in the range of values that was specified to their constructor. The behavior of this method when supplied values out of range is undefined, though in many cases classes will simply constrain the input value to the supported range.
        Parameters:
        z - a valid floating point value
        Returns:
        if a color is defined for z, its associated ARGB value; otherwise the null-value code.

      • getBaseColor

        public abstract Color getBaseColor()
        Gets the color for the minimum value in the range specified by this record. This method is intended primarily to support categorical palettes. It can also be useful in creating legends and keys in graphical presentations.
        Returns:
        a valid Color instance.

        public boolean isCovered(double z)

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        true if the value is within range; otherwise, false.

      • isTerminator

        public boolean isTerminator()
        Indicates whether the range of values for this instance is to be treated as "terminated". Normally, a value z is considered covered if it falls within the interval range0 <= z < range1. However, if the color record is the last one in a sequence, it may provide a color value for z = range1. In other words, if it terminates a sequence (is a terminator), it will provide a color value for z.
        Returns:
        true if the record terminates a sequence of records; otherwise, false.
